Thailand was one of the few countries in Asia where commercial surrogacy was not specifically banned by law.

There was however a regulation stating that doctors risk losing their license if they perform surrogacy for pay.

Thailand became a go-to destination for couples from Australia, Hong Kong and Taiwan and a low-cost alternative to the United States. 

