But Minister for Foreign Affairs Julie Bishop stepped in, negotiating with the Thai military to allow the couple caeess to the country and their children.

The Australian Department of Foreign Affairs estimated that 50 Thai surrogate mothers are expected to carry babies for Australian couples by the end of 2015.

There is currently a changeover period being debated to enable the children and their Australian parents to depart Thailand. 

 

  

 

 

